stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Manticore
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] 1 year
[Place of Birth] Sargon
[Date of Birth] Unknown
[Race] Manticore
[Height] 155cm
[Tail Length] 140cm
[Infection Status] 
Infection confirmed by medical examination.

[Physical Strength] Excellent 
[Mobility] Excellent 
[Physical Resilience] Standard 
[Tactical Acumen] Standard 
[Combat Skill] Excellent 
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Excellent

Much of Manticore's history is unknown. It is known that prior to her employment at Rhodes Island, she had engaged in the 'removal' of certain individuals. She has excellent stealth, infiltration, and surprise attack skills.
Now she serves as a special kind of Operator who provides these unique services for Rhodes Island.

Imaging tests have shown the outlines of her internal organs to be indistinct due to abnormal shadows. Originium granules have been detected in her circulatory system, confirming her to be infected with Oripathy.

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 12% 
Operator has no obvious ore lesions on the surface of her body. Tests have revealed the presence of crystals internally, however. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.32u/L 
Due to the presence of Originium within the Operator's internal organs, the Operator's shows an elevated blood crystal content.

Manticore is gentle, shy, and sometimes even gives others the feeling that she's afraid. She speaks in a hesitant tone and often stammers. She rarely finishes a sentence in one attempt, and she appears very stiff when communicating with other Operators. She would probably be more comfortable talking to a rock.
Additionally, her rare invisibility ability has become a major hindrance to communication. It has completely prevented her from improving her interpersonal skills. It may be necessary to suggest additional treatment solutions to help Manticore develop her social skills.

We communicate with Manticore by writing messages on paper. Oripathy has given her the ability to turn invisible (the report on this ability needs additional processing). It has been confirmed through interactive experiments that her ability does not transfer to inanimate objects, so paper communication has proved a suitable way to communicate with this operator.
After communication, Manticore likes to leave behind little gifts that smell sweetly of violets.

Manticore was born in Sargon. Because most of the background she provided could not be validated, Manticore's experience cannot be confirmed. What is known is that Manticore has undergone relatively comprehensive special operations training and has at least one year of operative experience under her belt.
The investigation into her special operations training unit was unsuccessful, and Sargon intelligence did not provide any valuable clues. Currently only unconfirmed and less than reliable intelligence from Sargon spies indicate there is a group of people who house Originium Arts users with special abilities in this area. These individuals are using special training methods to kill Sargon aristocrats or operatives from other nations.
Because of Manticore's vague background, she has been designated a special type of Oripathy patient at Rhodes Island. Any applications requesting use of Manticore in special operations or combat will first need to be submitted to Dr. Kal'tsit for approval.

[Manticore's Ability's Test Record] 
Test subject: Manticore. 
Test objective: To probe the usefulness of the subject's abilities and Originium Arts. 
Test content: To find Manticore while she is in hiding and to defend against her while she is in action. 
Test participants: An Operator who has worked with Manticore on several missions. 
Randomly select two Operators from all of the Operators available. 
Among them must be at least one technician Operator or non-technician Operator with high Originium adaptability. 
Test results: The test took place on a terrain simulating a complex environment. During the test period, none of the three Operators were able to locate the whereabouts of Manticore. When Manticore went on the offensive, some of the Operators managed to defend against her attacks using their quick reaction times and combat experience, while Manticore managed to successfully attack the others. 
Feedback results: According to the explanations provided by the Operators, Manticore could not be captured using visual means. Some of the Operators with better Originium adaptability reported feeling a strange atmosphere that instantly made them as though they were in danger. 
The above process has been recorded in its entirety. If you wish to view it, you must request it from the relevant department.

skins.description:
An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

<color name=#ffffff>EPOQUE Collection New Arrivals/Invisible Dirge. Taking the model's peculiar traits in consideration, this outfit was completed without being tailored. Combines comfort, fashion, and a proper fit while also protecting the operator's vitals.</color>
EPOQUE Sub-Brand [Passe] Series Selects/Under A Veil. Manticore once wore it on a mission in Sargon, and was bothered by the clanging of the gold accessories as she moved.

modules.desc:
Operator Manticore has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for bodily concealment and enemy ambush.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Specialist Operator during field operations to exercise Ambusher responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

A note stuck on the general store's warehouse door reads:
Sorry, I had to leave half an hour early today to see a doctor. I'm not feeling too good. I've been having a few sudden, intense aches, I think the part where I got scratched hasn't healed normally. I've already taken stock of everything for today, and those people who didn't like me didn't follow as far as the store. No worries.

A note stuck on the shabby bottle of perfume reads:
Thank you for always being with me all this time, and always being able to find me. This is a present for you. I know it's far from enough as a thank you, so if there's anything else I can do for you, please be sure to tell me right away.
Also, my sickness is mostly set to keep getting worse... If in time, this present can remind you of me every now and then, then I'm happy. It's alright if you can't remember me too.

A note fallen in the market's grit paving reads:
Hello, do you need help sorting out goods or cleaning up dust? I can do other work too. I'd like to work in exchange for some food. You might not notice where I am, but please don't worry. I'll do everything as earnestly as possible.

A note trapped beneath the dagger reads:
Mission complete.

A note stuck in the corner of the bulletin board of a Rhodes Island lounge, almost covered by the neighboring rainbow of stickers reads:
Everyone at the get-together sang very well. I didn't think it was one bit noisy. But if you decide to move to a more soundproofed room next time, could you put a notice up on the bulletin board beforehand?
Thank you to the person who recommended me drinks. I liked that sour and sweet dark orange one a lot.
—Manticore

voice_lines.voiceText: Umm, excuse me… I've been waiting here... for two hours…
Sorry… I know people keep ignoring me... But... my Arts aren't to blame…
My Arts... make me undetectable to people... in certain environments…
I… I've never had any friends... S-surely no one wants a friend that…  they can't even notice… right?
My tail... It curls up when I'm not fighting... So please, don't be afraid…
Doctor... you can leave the dangerous work to me... After all... my Arts were made for that…
These ID tags around my neck… I collected them... I like holding onto evidence... that someone once existed...
Don't let that 'Nightmare' girl near me!... She's dangerous... My Arts don't work on her... Why…?
I… I really want to cure my Oripathy. But if it's cured... what's going to happen to my Arts?... If they're gone, will I... still be of any use...?
Doctor's ignoring me… I don't like it, hmph...
I'm Manticore... My Arts can take out lives silently... Please don't be scared, you're not my target…
Thank you... I-I'm looking forward to you teaching me... more...
Finally, I got a promotion... I always thought I wasn't good enough… so you didn't promote me…
Did I... manage to help you? I don't have anywhere else to go... My home is here... at Rhodes Island... So please, let me protect it with you...
Okay...
Nobody will like me... as their captain...
Please don't leave me behind…
Please choose tactics that make use of my Arts... even if it's something crafty and underhanded... I won't mind...
I-I'm ready...
I'm…right here…
Manticore… going dark…
Ready... to ambush...
That must... really hurt…
Please, Don't come close…
I don't like this... either...
Farewell…
Even in such terrible battles… your judgement and decisions didn't seem to waver… You're incredible, Doctor…
A victory by all means... Still...
I can handle the runaways... if you wish...
I'm sorry... It's all my fault...
I'll sit... in the corner...
Eeeeeek!
Thank you for paying attention to me... I know it's your job... but it still makes me happy…
Arknights.
Happy New Year... More people have  noticed me... in the last year... I'm a little scared, but... a lot of them are very warm, and kind... So, I'm going to try as hard as I can... to adapt...
Hello... Doctor...
I'll just put the present on the table and leave... Doctor, happy birthday... Eek! Did-did you notice me...? Um, Happy birthday to you... Doctor.
I don't want to go through the experience... of losing a friend again... I will defend everyone, with my own life. Even if it's somewhere none of them will see me...
